  "text": "Storing quantum primitives as a list of time slices fits nicely with the previous requirements for quantum operators, e.g conjugation is easily achieved by iterating through the list in the reverse order and conjugating all its elements [CITATION_1] ; splicing (the third version of operator composition) requires constant time.",
